This paper is primarily focused on computer vision and deep learning techniques for object detection, specifically for detecting pedestrians, cyclists, and other riders in urban traffic scenes. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper discusses the optimization of deep learning approaches, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the potential for further research in improving object detection performance, which could fall under the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper discusses error sources and potential improvements in annotation quality, which could fall under the sub-category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
